images.summary: This section illustrates a typical foundation wall detail labeled CW8. The foundation wall is 8 inches thick and constructed of concrete, reinforced with 15M vertical rebar spaced at 48 inches on center, and horizontal rebar at the top and grade levels. A P.T. sill plate with a sill gasket is anchored with 1/2-inch diameter bolts at 48-inch intervals. The wall includes 2-inch rigid insulation (R-10) extending 24 inches below grade. The foundation rests on a continuous 24-inch by 8-inch strip footing, reinforced with two 15M continuous bars. The foundation is designed to bear on undisturbed native soil or compacted fill, as approved by a geotechnical engineer. Metal flashing is specified as per client requirements, and the grade slopes away from the building.
